{"word":"ὀφθαλμός","slug":"ὀφθαλμός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ὀφϑαλμός, οῦ, ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <el>ὄπωπα</el> (2 <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pf.\">pf.</a> of <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὁράω\">ὁράω</a></el>) and <el>ὄσσε</el> (dual form) ‘the two eyes’] <b>eye<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> as sensory organ <b><a href='B:470 5:29'>Mt 5:29</a>, <a href='B:470 5:38'>38</a>; <a href='B:470 6:22'>6:22f</a>; <a href='B:490 2:30'>Lk 2:30</a>; <a href='B:490 11:34'>11:34</a>; <a href='B:500 9:6'>J 9:6</a>; <a href='B:510 1:9'>Ac 1:9</a>; <a href='B:530 2:9'>1 Cor 2:9</a>; <a href='B:530 12:16'>12:16f</a>; <a href='B:550 4:15'>Gal 4:15</a>; <a href='B:650 4:13'>Hb 4:13</a>; <a href='B:680 2:14'>2 Pt 2:14</a>; <a href='B:690 1:1'>1 J 1:1</a>; <a href='B:730 1:7'>Rv 1:7</a>.</b> <el>ὀφϑαλμὸς <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:πονηρός\">πονηρός</a></el> eye filled with envy (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ prob.\">prob.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> connotation of attempt to cast a spell) <b><a href='B:480 7:22'>Mk 7:22</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> in imagery, of moral or spiritual understanding or perception <b><a href='B:470 13:15'>Mt 13:15f</a>; <a href='B:480 8:18'>Mk 8:18</a>; <a href='B:490 19:42'>Lk 19:42</a>; <a href='B:520 11:8'>Ro 11:8</a>; <a href='B:550 3:1'>Gal 3:1</a>; <a href='B:560 1:18'>Eph 1:18</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ὀφθαλμοδουλία\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ὀφθείς\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}